{
  "format": 1,
  "name": "Studio Delay",
  "isInstrument": false,
  "explanation": "A pristine rackmount digital delay. A fractionally-interpolated stereo delay line gives crystal-clear echoes that decay smoothly; feedback regenerates the repeats (bounded near maximum so it never runs away), an optional gentle modulation adds subtle movement, a high/low damping filter darkens or brightens each repeat, and a stereo width control offsets the left/right taps for a wide image. Controls: Time, Feedback, Modulation, Damping, Width and dry/wet Mix.",
  "params": [
    {
      "name": "Time",
      "index": 0,
      "min": 0,
      "max": 1,
      "default": 0.3
    },
    {
      "name": "Feedback",
      "index": 1,
      "min": 0,
      "max": 1,
      "default": 0.4
    },
    {
      "name": "Modulation",
      "index": 2,
      "min": 0,
      "max": 1,
      "default": 0.2
    },
    {
      "name": "Damping",
      "index": 3,
      "min": 0,
      "max": 1,
      "default": 0.55
    },
    {
      "name": "Width",
      "index": 4,
      "min": 0,
      "max": 1,
      "default": 0.35
    },
    {
      "name": "Mix",
      "index": 5,
      "min": 0,
      "max": 1,
      "default": 0.35
    }
  ],
  "wasmBase64": "",
  "html": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n  <title>Studio Delay</title>\n  <style>\n    :root {\n      --accent: #5ad1ff;\n      --accent2: #80c8ff;\n      --bg0: #0a0e14;\n      --bg1: #121823;\n      --panel: #1a2230;\n      --panel2: #222c3c;\n      --rail: #06090e;\n      --ink: #cdd9e6;\n      --ink-dim: #6b7a8d;\n      --led-off: #103040;\n    }\n\n    * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }\n\n    html, body {\n      height: 100%;\n      background: var(--bg0);\n      color: var(--ink);\n      font-family: ui-sans-serif, -apple-system, \"Segoe UI\", system-ui, sans-serif;\n      -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;\n    }\n\n    body {\n      display: flex;\n      align-items: center;\n      justify-content: center;\n      padding: 18px;\n      min-height: 100%;\n      background:\n        radial-gradient(1200px 500px at 50% -10%, rgba(90,209,255,0.08), transparent 60%),\n        linear-gradient(180deg, #0c111a 0%, #070a10 100%);\n    }\n\n    /* ---- the rack unit ---- */\n    .rack {\n      width: 100%;\n      max-width: 880px;\n      border-radius: 14px;\n      padding: 18px;\n      position: relative;\n      background: linear-gradient(180deg, #2a3543 0%, #161d28 100%);\n      box-shadow:\n        0 30px 70px rgba(0,0,0,0.6),\n        inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.08),\n        inset 0 -2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);\n      border: 1px solid #0b0f16;\n    }\n\n    /* rack ears / screws */\n    .screw {\n      position: absolute;\n      width: 14px; height: 14px;\n      border-radius: 50%;\n      background: radial-gradient(circle at 35% 30%, #5b6675, #1b2230 70%);\n      box-shadow: inset 0 1px 1px rgba(255,255,255,0.25), 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.6);\n    }\n    .screw::after {\n      content: \"\";\n      position: absolute;\n      inset: 4px;\n      border-radius: 50%;\n      background: linear-gradient(180deg, #0c1118, #2a323e);\n    }\n    .screw.tl { top: 10px; left: 10px; }\n    .screw.tr { top: 10px; right: 10px; }\n    .screw.bl { bottom: 10px; left: 10px; }\n    .screw.br { bottom: 10px; right: 10px; }\n\n    .faceplate {\n      border-radius: 9px;\n      padding: 16px 20px 20px;\n      background:\n        repeating-linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.012) 0 2px, transparent 2px 4px),\n        linear-gradient(180deg, #1d2734 0%, #141b26 100%);\n      border: 1px solid #0a0e15;\n      box-shadow: inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.05);\n      margin: 0 18px;\n    }\n\n    header {\n      display: flex;\n      align-items: center;\n      justify-content: space-between;\n      gap: 16px;\n      padding-bottom: 14px;\n      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05);\n    }\n\n    .brand { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; }\n\n    .logo-mark {\n      width: 34px; height: 34px;\n      border-radius: 8px;\n      display: grid;\n      place-items: center;\n      background: linear-gradient(160deg, #16202c, #0c121a);\n      border: 1px solid rgba(90,209,255,0.35);\n      box-shadow: 0 0 14px rgba(90,209,255,0.25), inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.06);\n    }\n    .logo-mark svg { display: block; }\n\n    .titles h1 {\n      font-size: 17px;\n      font-weight: 700;\n      letter-spacing: 3px;\n      text-transform: uppercase;\n      background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--accent), var(--accent2));\n      -webkit-background-clip: text;\n      background-clip: text;\n      color: transparent;\n    }\n    .titles .sub {\n      font-size: 9.5px;\n      letter-spacing: 4px;\n      text-transform: uppercase;\n      color: var(--ink-dim);\n      margin-top: 2px;\n    }\n\n    .model-badge {\n      font-size: 9px;\n      letter-spacing: 2px;\n      text-transform: uppercase;\n      color: var(--accent);\n      border: 1px solid rgba(90,209,255,0.3);\n      border-radius: 20px;\n      padding: 4px 11px;\n      background: rgba(90,209,255,0.06);\n    }\n\n    /* ---- segmented ms display ---- */\n    .display-wrap {\n      margin-top: 16px;\n      border-radius: 8px;\n      padding: 14px 18px;\n      background:\n        radial-gradient(120% 140% at 50% -20%, rgba(90,209,255,0.10), transparent 60%),\n        linear-gradient(180deg, #04080d, #02050a);\n      border: 1px solid #0a121b;\n      box-shadow: inset 0 2px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.85), inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(90,209,255,0.04);\n      display: flex;\n      align-items: center;\n      justify-content: space-between;\n      gap: 18px;\n      overflow: hidden;\n    }\n\n    .seg-block { display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 8px; }\n    .seg {\n      font-family: ui-monospace, \"SF Mono\", Menlo, Consolas, monospace;\n      font-size: 40px;\n      font-weight: 700;\n      letter-spacing: 2px;\n      font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n      color: var(--accent);\n      text-shadow: 0 0 8px rgba(90,209,255,0.65), 0 0 22px rgba(90,209,255,0.35);\n    }\n    .seg.dim {\n      color: rgba(90,209,255,0.18);\n      text-shadow: none;\n      position: absolute;\n    }\n    .seg-host { position: relative; }\n    .seg-unit {\n      font-size: 13px;\n      letter-spacing: 3px;\n      text-transform: uppercase;\n      color: var(--ink-dim);\n    }\n\n    /* tap indicator lane */\n    .taps {\n      flex: 1;\n      max-width: 360px;\n      display: flex;\n      align-items: center;\n      gap: 5px;\n      height: 46px;\n      padding: 0 4px;\n    }\n    .tap {\n      flex: 1;\n      height: 100%;\n      border-radius: 3px;\n      background: linear-gradient(180deg, #07131c, #050a10);\n      box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(90,209,255,0.05);\n      position: relative;\n      overflow: hidden;\n    }\n    .tap .fill {\n      position: absolute;\n      left: 0; right: 0; bottom: 0;\n      height: 0%;\n      background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--accent2), var(--accent));\n      box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(90,209,255,0.7);\n      transition: height 0.06s linear;\n    }\n\n    .status {\n      display: flex;\n      flex-direction: column;\n      align-items: flex-end;\n      gap: 6px;\n    }\n    .pwr {\n      display: flex;\n      align-items: center;\n      gap: 7px;\n      font-size: 9px;\n      letter-spacing: 2px;\n      text-transform: uppercase;\n      color: var(--ink-dim);\n    }\n    .pwr .dot {\n      width: 8px; height: 8px;\n      border-radius: 50%;\n      background: var(--accent);\n      box-shadow: 0 0 10px var(--accent);\n      animation: pulse 2.4s ease-in-out infinite;\n    }\n    @keyframes pulse {\n      0%, 100% { opacity: 1; box-shadow: 0 0 10px var(--accent); }\n      50% { opacity: 0.45; box-shadow: 0 0 4px var(--accent); }\n    }\n\n    /* ---- knob row ---- */\n    .controls {\n      margin-top: 20px;\n      display: grid;\n      grid-template-columns: repeat(6, 1fr);\n      gap: 10px;\n    }\n    @media (max-width: 700px) {\n      .controls { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); row-gap: 18px; }\n    }\n\n    .cell {\n      display: flex;\n      flex-direction: column;\n      align-items: center;\n      gap: 8px;\n      padding: 12px 6px 10px;\n      border-radius: 9px;\n      background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.02), rgba(0,0,0,0.18));\n      border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.03);\n    }\n\n    .knob {\n      width: 78px; height: 78px;\n      cursor: ns-resize;\n      position: relative;\n      touch-action: none;\n      user-select: none;\n    }\n    .knob svg { display: block; width: 100%; height: 100%; }\n    .knob .arc-fg { transition: stroke-dashoffset 0.05s linear; }\n\n    .label {\n      font-size: 9.5px;\n      letter-spacing: 2px;\n      text-transform: uppercase;\n      color: var(--ink-dim);\n    }\n    .value {\n      font-family: ui-monospace, \"SF Mono\", Menlo, Consolas, monospace;\n      font-size: 12px;\n      font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n      color: var(--ink);\n      min-height: 14px;\n    }\n    .cell:hover .label { color: var(--accent); }\n\n    .foot {\n      margin-top: 14px;\n      display: flex;\n      justify-content: space-between;\n      align-items: center;\n      font-size: 8.5px;\n      letter-spacing: 2px;\n      text-transform: uppercase;\n      color: var(--ink-dim);\n      padding: 0 4px;\n    }\n    .foot .vents {\n      display: flex; gap: 3px;\n    }\n    .foot .vents span {\n      width: 3px; height: 12px;\n      border-radius: 2px;\n      background: linear-gradient(180deg, #0a0f16, #05080d);\n      box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(255,255,255,0.03);\n    }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <div class=\"rack\">\n    <span class=\"screw tl\"></span>\n    <span class=\"screw tr\"></span>\n    <span class=\"screw bl\"></span>\n    <span class=\"screw br\"></span>\n\n    <div class=\"faceplate\">\n      <header>\n        <div class=\"brand\">\n          <div class=\"logo-mark\">\n            <svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"none\">\n              <path d=\"M2 10 H6 L8 4 L12 16 L14 10 H18\" stroke=\"#5ad1ff\" stroke-width=\"1.6\"\n                    stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"/>\n            </svg>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"titles\">\n            <h1>Studio Delay</h1>\n            <div class=\"sub\">Pristine Digital Echo · Stereo</div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"model-badge\">DDL-Series</div>\n      </header>\n\n      <div class=\"display-wrap\">\n        <div class=\"seg-block\">\n          <div class=\"seg-host\">\n            <span class=\"seg dim\">8888</span>\n            <span class=\"seg\" id=\"msReadout\">0300</span>\n          </div>\n          <span class=\"seg-unit\">ms</span>\n        </div>\n\n        <div class=\"taps\" id=\"taps\"></div>\n\n        <div class=\"status\">\n          <div class=\"pwr\"><span class=\"dot\"></span> Online</div>\n          <div class=\"pwr\" id=\"fbReadout\" style=\"animation:none\">FB 40%</div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"controls\" id=\"controls\"></div>\n\n      <div class=\"foot\">\n        <span>24-bit · 96kHz · Linear Interp</span>\n        <span class=\"vents\">\n          <span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span>\n        </span>\n        <span>Sync · Tap · Feedback Path</span>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <script>\n    \"use strict\";\n\n    // ---- parameter map (indices MUST match assembly.ts) ----\n    var PARAMS = [\n      { name: \"Time\",       index: 0, min: 0, max: 1, def: 0.30 },\n      { name: \"Feedback\",   index: 1, min: 0, max: 1, def: 0.40 },\n      { name: \"Modulation\", index: 2, min: 0, max: 1, def: 0.20 },\n      { name: \"Damping\",    index: 3, min: 0, max: 1, def: 0.55 },\n      { name: \"Width\",      index: 4, min: 0, max: 1, def: 0.35 },\n      { name: \"Mix\",        index: 5, min: 0, max: 1, def: 0.35 }\n    ];\n\n    var state = {};   // index -> normalized 0..1 value\n\n    // ---- value formatting per param ----\n    function formatValue(p, v) {\n      if (p.name === \"Time\") {\n        var ms = 20 + v * v * 1480;\n        return Math.round(ms) + \" ms\";\n      }\n      if (p.name === \"Damping\") {\n        if (v < 0.48) return \"Dark\";\n        if (v > 0.52) return \"Bright\";\n        return \"Flat\";\n      }\n      return Math.round(v * 100) + \" %\";\n    }\n\n    function pushParam(p, v) {\n      if (window.vstai && window.vstai.setParam) {\n        window.vstai.setParam(p.index, v);\n      }\n    }\n\n    // ---- build segmented ms display digit ghosting ----\n    function updateReadouts() {\n      var time = state[0];\n      var fb = state[1];\n      var ms = Math.round(20 + time * time * 1480);\n      var str = (\"0000\" + ms).slice(-4);\n      document.getElementById(\"msReadout\").textContent = str;\n      document.getElementById(\"fbReadout\").textContent = \"FB \" + Math.round(fb * 100) + \"%\";\n    }\n\n    // ---- knob factory (SVG) ----\n    var ARC_START = 135;   // degrees\n    var ARC_SWEEP = 270;\n    var R = 30;\n    var CIRC = 2 * Math.PI * R;\n\n    function makeKnob(p) {\n      var cell = document.createElement(\"div\");\n      cell.className = \"cell\";\n\n      var knob = document.createElement(\"div\");\n      knob.className = \"knob\";\n      knob.setAttribute(\"tabindex\", \"0\");\n\n      knob.innerHTML =\n        '<svg viewBox=\"0 0 80 80\">' +\n        '  <defs>' +\n        '    <radialGradient id=\"body' + p.index + '\" cx=\"40%\" cy=\"32%\" r=\"75%\">' +\n        '      <stop offset=\"0%\" stop-color=\"#2c3849\"/>' +\n        '      <stop offset=\"60%\" stop-color=\"#1b2431\"/>' +\n        '      <stop offset=\"100%\" stop-color=\"#0d1219\"/>' +\n        '    </radialGradient>' +\n        '  </defs>' +\n        '  <circle cx=\"40\" cy=\"40\" r=\"36\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#070b11\" stroke-width=\"6\"/>' +\n        '  <circle cx=\"40\" cy=\"40\" r=\"' + R + '\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#0c1620\" stroke-width=\"6\"' +\n        '    stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-dasharray=\"' + (CIRC * ARC_SWEEP / 360) + ' ' + CIRC + '\"' +\n        '    transform=\"rotate(' + ARC_START + ' 40 40)\"/>' +\n        '  <circle class=\"arc-fg\" cx=\"40\" cy=\"40\" r=\"' + R + '\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#5ad1ff\" stroke-width=\"6\"' +\n        '    stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-dasharray=\"' + CIRC + '\" stroke-dashoffset=\"' + CIRC + '\"' +\n        '    transform=\"rotate(' + ARC_START + ' 40 40)\"' +\n        '    style=\"filter:drop-shadow(0 0 4px rgba(90,209,255,0.8))\"/>' +\n        '  <circle cx=\"40\" cy=\"40\" r=\"23\" fill=\"url(#body' + p.index + ')\"' +\n        '    stroke=\"#3a4658\" stroke-width=\"1\"/>' +\n        '  <line class=\"pointer\" x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"40\" y2=\"22\" stroke=\"#9fe6ff\" stroke-width=\"2.6\"' +\n        '    stroke-linecap=\"round\"/>' +\n        '</svg>';\n\n      var label = document.createElement(\"div\");\n      label.className = \"label\";\n      label.textContent = p.name;\n\n      var value = document.createElement(\"div\");\n      value.className = \"value\";\n\n      cell.appendChild(knob);\n      cell.appendChild(label);\n      cell.appendChild(value);\n\n      var arc = knob.querySelector(\".arc-fg\");\n      var pointer = knob.querySelector(\".pointer\");\n\n      function render(v) {\n        var sweepLen = CIRC * ARC_SWEEP / 360;\n        arc.setAttribute(\"stroke-dashoffset\", String(CIRC - sweepLen * v));\n        var ang = ARC_START + v * ARC_SWEEP;\n        pointer.setAttribute(\"transform\", \"rotate(\" + ang + \" 40 40)\");\n        value.textContent = formatValue(p, v);\n      }\n\n      function setValue(v, push) {\n        v = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, v));\n        state[p.index] = v;\n        render(v);\n        if (push !== false) pushParam(p, v);\n        updateReadouts();\n      }\n\n      // drag (vertical)\n      var dragging = false;\n      var startY = 0, startV = 0;\n\n      function onDown(e) {\n        dragging = true;\n        startY = (e.touches ? e.touches[0].clientY : e.clientY);\n        startV = state[p.index];\n        e.preventDefault();\n      }\n      function onMove(e) {\n        if (!dragging) return;\n        var y = (e.touches ? e.touches[0].clientY : e.clientY);\n        var dy = startY - y;\n        var fine = e.shiftKey ? 0.25 : 1;\n        setValue(startV + dy / 200 * fine);\n        e.preventDefault();\n      }\n      function onUp() { dragging = false; }\n\n      knob.addEventListener(\"mousedown\", onDown);\n      window.addEventListener(\"mousemove\", onMove);\n      window.addEventListener(\"mouseup\", onUp);\n      knob.addEventListener(\"touchstart\", onDown, { passive: false });\n      window.addEventListener(\"touchmove\", onMove, { passive: false });\n      window.addEventListener(\"touchend\", onUp);\n\n      knob.addEventListener(\"wheel\", function (e) {\n        var step = (e.shiftKey ? 0.005 : 0.02) * (e.deltaY < 0 ? 1 : -1);\n        setValue(state[p.index] + step);\n        e.preventDefault();\n      }, { passive: false });\n\n      knob.addEventListener(\"dblclick\", function () {\n        setValue(p.def);\n      });\n\n      knob.addEventListener(\"keydown\", function (e) {\n        if (e.key === \"ArrowUp\" || e.key === \"ArrowRight\") { setValue(state[p.index] + 0.02); e.preventDefault(); }\n        if (e.key === \"ArrowDown\" || e.key === \"ArrowLeft\") { setValue(state[p.index] - 0.02); e.preventDefault(); }\n      });\n\n      p._setValue = setValue;\n      return cell;\n    }\n\n    // ---- build tap indicator lane (animated echo decay) ----\n    var TAP_COUNT = 14;\n    var tapFills = [];\n\n    function buildTaps() {\n      var lane = document.getElementById(\"taps\");\n      for (var i = 0; i < TAP_COUNT; i++) {\n        var t = document.createElement(\"div\");\n        t.className = \"tap\";\n        var f = document.createElement(\"div\");\n        f.className = \"fill\";\n        t.appendChild(f);\n        lane.appendChild(t);\n        tapFills.push(f);\n      }\n    }\n\n    // animation: a pulse travels across the taps, decaying by feedback amount.\n    var animPos = 0;\n    var lastT = 0;\n    function animate(ts) {\n      if (document.hidden) { requestAnimationFrame(animate); lastT = ts; return; }\n      if (!lastT) lastT = ts;\n      var dt = (ts - lastT) / 1000;\n      lastT = ts;\n\n      var time = state[0] != null ? state[0] : 0.3;\n      var fb = state[1] != null ? state[1] : 0.4;\n      var mix = state[5] != null ? state[5] : 0.35;\n\n      // speed of the travelling pulse scales with delay time (longer = slower)\n      var ms = 20 + time * time * 1480;\n      var speed = 9.0 / (0.25 + ms / 400);   // taps per second\n      animPos += dt * speed;\n      if (animPos >= TAP_COUNT + 4) animPos = 0;\n\n      for (var i = 0; i < TAP_COUNT; i++) {\n        // each tap lights as the pulse passes, repeats fade by feedback\n        var d = i - animPos;\n        var amp = 0;\n        // primary pass\n        var head = Math.exp(-Math.abs(d) * 1.6);\n        amp = head;\n        // echo trail behind, attenuated by feedback\n        if (d < 0) {\n          amp = head * (0.4 + fb * 0.6);\n        }\n        var decay = Math.pow(0.55 + fb * 0.4, i * 0.5);\n        var h = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, amp * decay)) * (0.3 + mix * 0.7);\n        tapFills[i].style.height = (h * 100) + \"%\";\n      }\n      requestAnimationFrame(animate);\n    }\n\n    // ---- init ----\n    function start() {\n      var host = document.getElementById(\"controls\");\n      for (var i = 0; i < PARAMS.length; i++) {\n        var p = PARAMS[i];\n        host.appendChild(makeKnob(p));\n      }\n      buildTaps();\n      // initialise every param to its default and push once\n      for (var j = 0; j < PARAMS.length; j++) {\n        PARAMS[j]._setValue(PARAMS[j].def, true);\n      }\n      updateReadouts();\n      requestAnimationFrame(animate);\n    }\n\n    if (window.vstai && window.vstai.onReady) {\n      window.vstai.onReady(start);\n    } else {\n      start();\n    }\n  </script>\n</body>\n</html>\n",
  "assembly": "// =====================================================================\n//  STUDIO DELAY — pristine rackmount DIGITAL delay (effect)\n//  A crystal-clear stereo delay: a fractionally-interpolated delay line\n//  with feedback, an optional gentle modulation of the read head, and a\n//  shelving high/low damping that gradually darkens (or brightens) the\n//  repeats. A stereo offset spreads the left/right taps for width. This\n//  is a CLEAN digital echo — no tape wow, no bucket-brigade grit — that\n//  decays smoothly and stays bounded even near maximum feedback.\n//  Pure algorithm, no samples.\n// =====================================================================\n\nconst MAX_FRAMES: i32 = 8192;\nconst MAX_CHANNELS: i32 = 2;\nconst MAX_PARAMS: i32 = 64;\n\nconst inBuf:  StaticArray<f32> = new StaticArray<f32>(MAX_FRAMES * MAX_CHANNELS);\nconst outBuf: StaticArray<f32> = new StaticArray<f32>(MAX_FRAMES * MAX_CHANNELS);\nconst params: StaticArray<f32> = new StaticArray<f32>(MAX_PARAMS);\n\n// Delay line: ~2.0 s per channel at 96k is plenty (max time 1.5 s here).\nconst MAX_DELAY: i32 = 192000;           // 2.0 s @ 96k, per channel\nconst delayL: StaticArray<f32> = new StaticArray<f32>(MAX_DELAY);\nconst delayR: StaticArray<f32> = new StaticArray<f32>(MAX_DELAY);\n\nlet sampleRate: f32 = 48000.0;\nlet channels: i32 = 2;\n\nlet writePos: i32 = 0;                    // shared circular write head\nlet smoothTimeL: f32 = 12000.0;           // smoothed delay length (samples), L\nlet smoothTimeR: f32 = 12000.0;           // smoothed delay length (samples), R\nlet lpStateL: f32 = 0.0;                  // damping low-pass state in feedback path\nlet lpStateR: f32 = 0.0;\nlet hpStateL: f32 = 0.0;                  // damping high-pass state in feedback path\nlet hpStateR: f32 = 0.0;\nlet modPhase: f32 = 0.0;                  // modulation LFO phase 0..1\n\n// Parameter indices --------------------------------------------------\nconst P_TIME: i32 = 0;        // 0..1 -> 20 ms .. 1500 ms base delay\nconst P_FEEDBACK: i32 = 1;    // 0..1 -> 0 .. 0.95 regeneration\nconst P_MOD: i32 = 2;         // 0..1 -> modulation depth (subtle)\nconst P_DAMP: i32 = 3;        // 0..1 -> 0 = dark repeats .. 0.5 flat .. 1 = bright\nconst P_WIDTH: i32 = 4;       // 0..1 -> stereo offset between L/R taps\nconst P_MIX: i32 = 5;         // 0..1 -> dry/wet\n\nconst PI: f32 = 3.14159265;\nconst TWO_PI: f32 = 6.2831853;\n\nexport function init(sr: f32, maxFrames: i32, numChannels: i32): void {\n  sampleRate = sr > 0.0 ? sr : 48000.0;\n  channels = numChannels < MAX_CHANNELS ? numChannels : MAX_CHANNELS;\n  for (let i = 0; i < MAX_DELAY; i++) { delayL[i] = 0.0; delayR[i] = 0.0; }\n  writePos = 0;\n  smoothTimeL = 0.25 * sampleRate;\n  smoothTimeR = 0.25 * sampleRate;\n  lpStateL = 0.0; lpStateR = 0.0;\n  hpStateL = 0.0; hpStateR = 0.0;\n  modPhase = 0.0;\n  params[P_TIME] = 0.30;\n  params[P_FEEDBACK] = 0.40;\n  params[P_MOD] = 0.20;\n  params[P_DAMP] = 0.55;\n  params[P_WIDTH] = 0.35;\n  params[P_MIX] = 0.35;\n}\n\nexport function getInputPtr(): usize  { return changetype<usize>(inBuf); }\nexport function getOutputPtr(): usize { return changetype<usize>(outBuf); }\nexport function getParamsPtr(): usize { return changetype<usize>(params); }\nexport function getNumParams(): i32   { return 6; }\n\n@inline function clampf(x: f32, lo: f32, hi: f32): f32 { return x < lo ? lo : (x > hi ? hi : x); }\n\n// Read the delay line at a fractional sample distance behind the write head,\n// with linear interpolation. `dist` is in samples (>= 1).\n@inline function readDelay(line: StaticArray<f32>, dist: f32): f32 {\n  let d: f32 = dist;\n  if (d < 1.0) d = 1.0;\n  const fMax: f32 = f32(MAX_DELAY - 2);\n  if (d > fMax) d = fMax;\n  // read position = writePos - d (mod MAX_DELAY)\n  let rp: f32 = f32(writePos) - d;\n  while (rp < 0.0) rp += f32(MAX_DELAY);\n  const i0: i32 = i32(rp);\n  let i1: i32 = i0 + 1; if (i1 >= MAX_DELAY) i1 -= MAX_DELAY;\n  const frac: f32 = rp - f32(i0);\n  const a: f32 = line[i0];\n  const b: f32 = line[i1];\n  return f32(a + (b - a) * frac);\n}\n\nexport function process(n: i32): void {\n  const timeN: f32 = clampf(params[P_TIME], 0.0, 1.0);\n  const fbN: f32 = clampf(params[P_FEEDBACK], 0.0, 1.0);\n  const modN: f32 = clampf(params[P_MOD], 0.0, 1.0);\n  const dampN: f32 = clampf(params[P_DAMP], 0.0, 1.0);\n  const widthN: f32 = clampf(params[P_WIDTH], 0.0, 1.0);\n  const mix: f32 = clampf(params[P_MIX], 0.0, 1.0);\n\n  // Base delay 20 ms .. 1500 ms (quadratic feel for fine control on short times)\n  const baseMs: f32 = 20.0 + timeN * timeN * 1480.0;\n  let baseSamp: f32 = baseMs * 0.001 * sampleRate;\n  const maxSamp: f32 = f32(MAX_DELAY - 4);\n  if (baseSamp > maxSamp) baseSamp = maxSamp;\n  if (baseSamp < 2.0) baseSamp = 2.0;\n\n  // Stereo offset: spread R tap a little longer for a wider image.\n  const offset: f32 = widthN * 0.020 * sampleRate;     // up to 20 ms spread\n  let targetL: f32 = baseSamp;\n  let targetR: f32 = baseSamp + offset;\n  if (targetR > maxSamp) targetR = maxSamp;\n\n  // Feedback up to 0.95 — bounded (never self-oscillates to infinity).\n  const fb: f32 = fbN * 0.95;\n\n  // Damping: a one-pole low-pass + a gentle high-pass in the feedback path.\n  // dampN < 0.5 -> darker (lower LP cutoff); dampN > 0.5 -> brighter.\n  // LP cutoff sweeps 1.2 kHz .. 18 kHz.\n  const lpHz: f32 = 1200.0 + dampN * dampN * 16800.0;\n  let lpC: f32 = f32(1.0 - Mathf.exp(-TWO_PI * lpHz / sampleRate));\n  lpC = clampf(lpC, 0.0, 1.0);\n  // Static high-pass ~110 Hz keeps low-end build-up out of the repeats.\n  let hpC: f32 = f32(1.0 - Mathf.exp(-TWO_PI * 110.0 / sampleRate));\n  hpC = clampf(hpC, 0.0, 1.0);\n\n  // Modulation: subtle ~0.35 Hz chorus-like detune of the read head.\n  const modHz: f32 = 0.35;\n  const modInc: f32 = modHz / sampleRate;\n  const modDepth: f32 = modN * 0.0025 * sampleRate;     // up to ~2.5 ms swing\n\n  // Per-sample smoothing coefficient for delay-time changes (zipper-free).\n  const timeSmooth: f32 = 0.0008;\n\n  let tL: f32 = smoothTimeL;\n  let tR: f32 = smoothTimeR;\n  let lpL: f32 = lpStateL;\n  let lpR: f32 = lpStateR;\n  let hpL: f32 = hpStateL;\n  let hpR: f32 = hpStateR;\n  let mph: f32 = modPhase;\n\n  const baseL: i32 = 0;\n  const baseR: i32 = MAX_FRAMES;\n\n  for (let f = 0; f < n; f++) {\n    const inL: f32 = inBuf[baseL + f];\n    const inR: f32 = channels > 1 ? inBuf[baseR + f] : inL;\n\n    // Smooth toward target delay lengths.\n    tL += timeSmooth * (targetL - tL);\n    tR += timeSmooth * (targetR - tR);\n\n    // Modulation LFO (sine), L & R in slight quadrature for movement.\n    mph += modInc; if (mph >= 1.0) mph -= 1.0;\n    const modL: f32 = f32(Mathf.sin(TWO_PI * mph)) * modDepth;\n    const modR: f32 = f32(Mathf.sin(TWO_PI * mph + 1.5708)) * modDepth;\n\n    let distL: f32 = tL + modL;\n    let distR: f32 = tR + modR;\n    if (distL < 1.0) distL = 1.0;\n    if (distR < 1.0) distR = 1.0;\n\n    // Read the echoes.\n    const echoL: f32 = readDelay(delayL, distL);\n    const echoR: f32 = readDelay(delayR, distR);\n\n    // Feedback signal = input + echo*fb, then damp before re-writing.\n    let fbL: f32 = inL + echoL * fb;\n    let fbR: f32 = inR + echoR * fb;\n\n    // Low-pass (darken) in the feedback path.\n    lpL += lpC * (fbL - lpL);\n    lpR += lpC * (fbR - lpR);\n    // High-pass = signal minus its slow component.\n    hpL += hpC * (lpL - hpL);\n    hpR += hpC * (lpR - hpR);\n    const wL: f32 = lpL - hpL;\n    const wR: f32 = lpR - hpR;\n\n    // Safety soft-limit on what we feed back so it can't blow up.\n    let writeL: f32 = wL;\n    let writeR: f32 = wR;\n    if (writeL > 1.5) writeL = 1.5; else if (writeL < -1.5) writeL = -1.5;\n    if (writeR > 1.5) writeR = 1.5; else if (writeR < -1.5) writeR = -1.5;\n\n    delayL[writePos] = writeL;\n    delayR[writePos] = writeR;\n\n    // Output: dry + wet echoes.\n    const wetL: f32 = echoL;\n    const wetR: f32 = echoR;\n    let oL: f32 = inL * (1.0 - mix) + wetL * mix;\n    let oR: f32 = inR * (1.0 - mix) + wetR * mix;\n\n    // Final clean ceiling (keeps peak < ~1.0 even with stacked repeats).\n    if (oL > 0.999) oL = 0.999; else if (oL < -0.999) oL = -0.999;\n    if (oR > 0.999) oR = 0.999; else if (oR < -0.999) oR = -0.999;\n\n    outBuf[baseL + f] = oL;\n    outBuf[baseR + f] = oR;\n\n    writePos++; if (writePos >= MAX_DELAY) writePos = 0;\n  }\n\n  smoothTimeL = tL;\n  smoothTimeR = tR;\n  lpStateL = lpL; lpStateR = lpR;\n  hpStateL = hpL; hpStateR = hpR;\n  modPhase = mph;\n}\n",
  "publishedAt": 1751000069000
}